<item>
            <title>[HBASE-379] [hbase] Allow column families with an unlimited number of versions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-379</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For some applications, you&apos;ll want to be able to create column families that never eliminate their old version, essentially keeping a permanent record. We should support this option when creating a table, or if it already exists, it should be documented.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12384110">HBASE-379</key>
            <summary>[hbase] Allow column families with an unlimited number of versions</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png">Bug</type>
