                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12549163" author="jimk" created="Thu, 6 Dec 2007 20:04:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You can do that today. The maximum number of versions allowed in a column is Integer.MAX_VALUE&lt;br/&gt;
2 billion versions should be enough.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12549172" author="bryanduxbury" created="Thu, 6 Dec 2007 20:28:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integer.MAX_VALUE would be fine when you&apos;re coding in Java, but we need something for the shell. Could we do:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;code&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
CREATE TABLE whatever (&apos;column_fam&apos; MAX_VERSIONS=-1);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or something like that?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12549186" author="jimk" created="Thu, 6 Dec 2007 20:52:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the shell that would be ok, provided it converted it to Integer.MAX_VALUE&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12550372" author="udanax" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2007 09:36:37 +0000"  >&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;modified INTEGER_LITERAL in parser (a sign plus, a sign minus)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MAX_VERSIONS=-1 will be change to (2 &lt;sup&gt;31&lt;/sup&gt; -1).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12550374" author="udanax" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2007 09:37:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;submitting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
